.TH LUNIS 1 "2026-01-02" "Lunis CLI" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lunis \- Lunar/sexagenary calendar converter

.SH DESCRIPTION
Converts a Gregorian date to the Chinese/Vietnamese/Japanese/Korean lunar calendar.

The tool supports two modes:

.TP
convert
Reads a date from standard input in \fBRFC 3339\fP format, e.g., `2026-03-02T23:40:33+07:00`. 
You can pipe input like:

.nf
$ date -Iseconds | lunis convert -l vi -f "{y-s} {y-b} - {m-s} {m-b} ({m-S}) - {d-s} {d-b} | Giờ {h-b} - {ke} khắc"
.fi

.TP
now
Uses the \fBcurrent system time\fP as input. For example:

.nf
$ lunis now -l zh -f "{y-s} {y-b} - {m-S} - {d-s} {d-b} | Giờ {h-b} - {ke}"
.fi

.TP
Timezone handling
The tool \fBignores the timezone\fP of the input date. All calculations are based solely on the provided datetime values, without conversion between zones.

.SH USAGE 
lunis convert|now [OPTIONS]

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
-l, --lang <LANG>
Language for output: vi, zh, ko, jp
.TP
-f, --format <FORMAT>
Format string for output (see below)
.SH FORMAT STRING
Your format string supports placeholders:

.TP
\{y-s\} / \{y-b\} / \{y-y\} / \{y-w\} / \{y-n\}
Year: stem, branch, yinyang, wuxing, number

.TP
\{m-s\} / \{m-b\} / \{m-y\} / \{m-w\} / \{m-n\} / \{m-S\}
Month: stem, branch, yinyang, wuxing, number, string (e.g., "Tháng Giêng", "闰三月")

.TP
\{d-s\} / \{d-b\} / \{d-y\} / \{d-w\} / \{d-n\}
Day: stem, branch, yinyang, wuxing, number

.TP
\{h-s\} / \{h-b\} / \{h-y\} / \{h-w\} / \{h-n\}
Hour: stem, branch, yinyang, wuxing, number (0–23)

.TP
\{ke\}
15-minute ke of the hours (0–7)

.SH EXAMPLES
Convert a date with Vietnamese output:

.nf
$ echo "2026-03-02T23:40:33+07:00" | lunis convert -l vi -f "{y-s} {y-b} - {m-s} {m-b} ({m-S}) - {d-s} {d-b} | Giờ {h-b} - {ke} khắc"
Bính Ngọ - Canh Dần (Tháng Giêng) - Ất Hợi | Giờ Tý - 2 khắc
.fi

.SH SEE ALSO
date(1), cal(1)
